ISLAMABAD, March 1 (Xinhua) -- At least seven people were killed after a clash in Shikarpur district of Pakistan's southern Sindh province, local media reported on Tuesday. According to the ARY news, the killings occurred as a result of crossfires between two groups. Both the parties exchanged heavy cross-fire while also using rocket launchers, police told local media. The reason for the clash was old enmity, police said, adding that all the deceased had been identified. Reportedly, police reached the site after the incident and started an investigation.  â– 